<h3><a name=next>Now what?</a></h3>
<p>You've now got a shiny new, modern version of the latest stable Perl. So what next?</p>

<h4>cpanm</h4>
<p>cpan is a huge collection of open source, massively well tested libraries of code you can use to do all kinds of things. [Mojo, ...]</p>
<p><b>cpanm</b> is how you get them installed.  It's like Ruby's <code>gems</code> or Python's <code>??</code></p>
<p>This will install a rockin' web development environment, called Mojolicious.  Just type it into your Terminal window.</p>
<pre><code>cpanm Mojolicious</code></pre>

